According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Cerium Oxide Abrasive market was valued at USD 36.3 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 39.1 million in 2025 to USD 56.7 million by 2031, registering a CAGR of 6.7% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady expansion due to increasing demand for high-precision polishing materials across semiconductor manufacturing, optical components, consumer electronics, and photovoltaic applications.
Cerium oxide abrasives are widely recognized for their superior polishing efficiency and exceptional surface finishing capabilities. Available in slurry and powder forms, these materials are extensively used for polishing optical lenses, glass substrates, semiconductor wafers, hard disks, and photomasks. Growing investments in advanced electronics manufacturing, increasing production of high-performance optical components, and continuous innovation in abrasive formulations are supporting market growth worldwide.
